He further urged members of the public to observe all precautionary measures as the government is doing all it takes to contain the spread of the virus. Vanguard reports that Taraba still has 11 active COVID-19 cases. vanguard Taraba state said it has apprehended the positive COVID-19 patient who last week fled the isolation centre where she and seven others were being treated. May 4, 2020 In "News" Taraba state said it has apprehended the positive COVID-19 patient who last week fled the isolation centre where she and seven others were being treated. May 4, 2020 In "News" One positive patient of COVID-19 in Taraba state have escaped from the state's isolation centre. Chairman of the state COVID-19 technical committee and state Commissioner for Health, Dr Innocent Vakkai disclosed this Saturday at a briefing in Jalingo. He gave the name of the fleeing patient as Talatu Idris. May 2, 2020 In "News"